                                 OkHttpClient okHttpClient,
                                 java.lang.String secret)
        Parameters:
        url -
        Returns:
        An Object which is either a JSONObject or JSONArray. You can check exactly which using JSONTokener.

        Example: 

         
 Object json = new JSONTokener(getMappedInResult(url)).nextValue();
 if (json instanceof JSONObject) {
     // you have an JSON object
 } else if (json instanceof JSONArray) {
     // you have an JSON array
 }
